#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:15
msgid "General rules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:17
msgid "**To select something**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:20
msgid ""
"Use the mouse. IMPORTANT: **Mouse must be in pointer mode**. For this, click"
" on the button |mouse_mode_selection_24| in the toolbox."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:21
msgid ""
"Select one object: Clicking on an object with the left button selects it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:22
msgid "Select many objects:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:24
msgid ""
"Clicking while having pressed key :kbd:`Ctrl` adds clicked object to current"
" selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:25
msgid "Dragging a box around an area selects all objects in that area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:28
msgid "**Contextual menus**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:31
msgid ""
"By clicking with the mouse right button on any object (:redbold:`mouse must "
"be in pointer mode`), a contextual menu will be displayed. It contains "
"specific actions for that object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:37
msgid "**To delete an object**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:40
msgid "Select it with the mouse (click on it or drag around it)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:41
msgid ""
"Either, press delete key :kbd:`Del` or click Cut either on contextual menu, "
"on main menu, or in toolbar |tool_cut_24|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:42
msgid ""
"Also, if you make a mistake when entering notes, rests or when doing any "
"other action, press :kbd:`Ctrl` + :kbd:`z` to undo last action (or, choose "
"**Edit > Undo**). You can undo as many steps as you like."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:45
msgid "**To enter music symbols in the score**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:48
msgid ""
"Entering music begins with selecting the data entry mouse mode in the "
"toolbox. To do it you must click on the button |mouse_mode_data_entry_24|."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:54
msgid ""
"Then you must select the palette that contains the symbol you would like To "
"add. To select a palette you must either use one of the keys :kbd:`F2` to "
":kbd:`F12` or click on the palette selection button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:60
msgid ""
"Next step is to select a symbol from a palette by clicking on it with the "
"mouse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:63
msgid ""
"Finally, move the mouse to the score, to the place where you would like the "
"symbol to be added, and click on that point. In order to show you valid "
"places to drop the selected object, different mouse cursors are used to "
"guide the process. The mouse cursor ensures that you place symbols in "
"meaningful locations and provide additional visual feedback about the action"
" that is being performed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/score/general-rules.txt:66
msgid ""
"When you add music symbols to the score the program properly aligns and "
"positions them according to standard music notation rules. Notes are beamed "
"together or flagged, rests are added around notes, measures resized, etc. in"
" order to get the music to fit properly."
msgstr ""
